The menu of a greedy child: it does not breakfast and eats sausage for the evening bread
More than a third of children from 9 to 13 have overweight problems, with 9% of all students and 5% of all children being overweight.
Current surveys have shown that, most of the children are from families with unhealthy lifestyle.
This shows once again how important for the healthy development of a human being is the environment in which he grows up and the examples that surround him.
On the tables of adipous children, sausages are up to half more common on the table than in families in which normal children live.
More than 19 percent of the overweight children had on the eve of the education action under the motto "Adipositas is no coincidence" to the evening bread.
In families with fat ones, sport is not exactly one of the most popular activities, but as far as the majority of today's students are concerned, only 15 percent answered that their parents find time for active movement at least once a week.
Survey among 900 children
The survey took place last year towards the end of the school year, with nearly 900 children from primary schools in the Czech Republic being interviewed.
This was the second year of the action "Adipositas is not a coincidence," which is supported by the General Health Fund and the Unilever Society.
To date, more than 12 thousand students from 4 and 8 classes have participated in the project.
Unhealthy food and lack of movement in the family are crucial factors responsible for the frightening increase in the number of children with overweight or even obesity.
"Only half of the children interviewed, for example, said, five times a day, in the mode of eating breakfast-second breakfast-lunch-Vesper evening bread - one of the main conditions for a healthy diet," is one of the survey results.
No breakfast and sausage for dinner
Experts point out that relative small things, such as the regular breakfast time of the family, are also important for the healthy development of a child.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23% of the families of the students had breakfast.
And - in most families, everyone has breakfast on their own.
The worst was the finding that every tenth family does not have breakfast at all.
Breakfast is considered the basis of healthy daily diet.
The survey showed, among other things, that in the families you consume overweight children much more often unhealthy fries.
And almost everyone - without regard to weight - drinks sweet lemonades every day (70 percent)
Although more than 40 percent of the children interviewed are sports, only less than half of their parents do - that is, only 15 percent.
Set up your own menu
Another part of the survey made it possible for selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to set up their own food plan from the possibilities offered by appetite and opinion.
"What Czech children prefer between 12 and 15 in terms of nutrition is far from the ideal of a healthy diet.
Among their favorite dishes were many meals of flour, meat dishes and, of course, sweet food.
"Alarmingly, the great popularity of sweet lemonades is above all," is highlighted in the final report on this survey.
At lunch, the main dish, pasta was won just before poultry.
The children almost didn't like legumes and the popularity of fish and vegetable dishes as lunch was very low.
Return to health
At the same time, however, the survey also showed that the children are willing to change their eating habits when they get proper information.
"In the survey group, which completed the questionnaire after the opening of the" Adipositas is not a coincidence, "there was in many cases a significant shift in preferences towards the principles of healthy nutrition," is mentioned in the project's results.
This was the case for example with the sweet Limos, where many children began to give priority to ordinary water.
In the questionnaire, the children also crossed much more often poultry or fish as the main dish of the day and were prepared to eat less noodles or sweet food.
