The program includes the composition of the important Czech Jazzer Karel Růžička "Celebration Jazz Mass."
In the evening hours, in the gallery rooms of the People's House in Vinohrady, the concert "Students of the Holy Revolution" (Studenty sametu) is not excluded from the choirs of the Charles University.
Festa Academica is the goal not only to celebrate the World Student Day and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Holy Revolution, but to present choir music to the public at the highest level and to promote the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organiser is the association of Czech choirs in cooperation with the Johannes-Kepler-Gymnasium.
Bohuslav Svoboda, the mayor of the capital Prague and Václav Hampl, the rector of the Charles University, took over the patronage of the entire event.
The festival will take place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and in Pardubice.
The schedule includes also numerous music meetings, student happenings, matinees and other events.
Detailed information can be found on the website of the festival www.festaacademica.cz
