This leader then even put the founder of IBM in the shadows - based on Watson's ideas to this day, the invincible culture and identity of the company.
Watson led the company until 1952.
IBM, as the name suggests, began with the production and distribution of all possible machines for trade - from sausage and cheese cutting, to cash.
