For example, under the following conditions, the votes contained in one or more electoral packages may be counted in part. The results in the protocols do not agree; the minutes on the census and calculation of votes are not in fact available or it is not in the possession of the chairman of the electoral committee or there are obvious errors or amendments in the protocols.
In addition, the total number of the full-filled ballot cards may be taken when there is a difference between the expected winner and the second-place winner, equal to or less than one percent, provided that at the beginning of the meeting there is an explicit request from the party or coalition president, who is the second of the above-mentioned candidates.
The number of votes may also be taken as a whole if, after the completion of the regular calculation, it is established that the difference between the expected winner and the candidate in second place is equal to or less than one percent, provided that an explicit request is made by a representative of the party whose candidate has become second. In this case, the electoral packages that have been subjected to a partial counting would be excluded.
