The Guardia Urbana (urban police) also confirmed that in recent weeks it has received more complaints from the neighbours.
The President of the PP (Partido Popular - People's Party) at the Barcelona City Council, Alberto Fernández Díaz, had asked for the building to be cleared up immediately last week and for the problems of civil coexistence and the fall of the district to be taken into account.
